hands_on_practices.solution:
We wish to minimize
$$f(p)=\frac{E_p}{p}\,,\qquad E_p=\sqrt{\Bigl(\frac{p_F}{m}(p-p_F)\Bigr)^2+\Delta^2}\,,\quad p0\,. $$

1.  Critical point from 
$$\frac{df}{dp}=0\quad\Longrightarrow\quad p\,\frac{dE_p}{dp}=E_p\,. $$

2.  Compute
$$\frac{dE_p}{dp}
=\frac{\bigl(\frac{p_F}{m}\bigr)^2(p-p_F)}{E_p}\,. $$

3.  Setting $p\,dE_p/dp=E_p$ gives
$$p\frac{\bigl(\frac{p_F}{m}\bigr)^2(p-p_F)}{E_p}=E_p
\;\Longrightarrow\;
p\Bigl(\tfrac{p_F}{m}\Bigr)^2(p-p_F)
=(\tfrac{p_F}{m})^2(p-p_F)^2+\Delta^2\,. $$

4.  Simplify by dividing by $(p_F/m)^2$:
$$p(p-p_F)=(p-p_F)^2+\frac{\Delta^2}{(p_F/m)^2}
\;\Longrightarrow\;
p_F(p-p_F)=\frac{\Delta^2}{(p_F/m)^2}\,. $$

5.  Hence the extremal momentum is
$$p^*=p_F+\frac{\Delta^2}{p_F\,(p_F/m)^2}
=p_F+\frac{m^2\Delta^2}{p_F^3}\,. $$

6.  At $p^*$ the excitation energy is
$$E_{p^*}
=\sqrt{\Bigl(\tfrac{p_F}{m}\Bigr)^2\Bigl(\tfrac{\Delta^2}{p_F(p_F/m)^2}\Bigr)^2+\Delta^2}
=\Delta\sqrt{1+\frac{m^2\Delta^2}{p_F^4}}\,. $$

7.  Therefore the Landau critical velocity is
$$v_c=\frac{E_{p^*}}{p^*}
=\frac{\Delta\sqrt{1+\frac{m^2\Delta^2}{p_F^4}}}
{\,p_F\Bigl(1+\frac{m^2\Delta^2}{p_F^4}\Bigr)}
=\frac{\Delta}{p_F\sqrt{1+\frac{m^2\Delta^2}{p_F^4}}}
=\frac{\Delta\,p_F}{\sqrt{p_F^4+m^2\Delta^2}}\,. $$
